I'm a little late to the party but I believe I've found the root cause. Per OpenXML spec, a custom 'totalsRowFormula' in a table column will add a child element in the column XML element; however, the code in `table-column-xform.js` expects columns to be leaf nodes. As `XLSX.load()` parses the table, any such columns are not recognized by the parser and do not find their way into `this.map.tableColumns.model`. However, `this.map.autoFilter.model.columns` does have the correct number of columns. This mismatch causes a index overrun in this loop (around line 101 in table-xform.js):
```
          this.map.autoFilter.model.columns.forEach((column, index) => {
            this.model.columns[index].filterButton = column.filterButton;
          });
```

Without a fix there's no real workaround other than to remove custom totals row formulas from all tables.
